ğŸ”„ CI/CD Pipeline Flow
1ï¸âƒ£ Code Push

Developer pushes code to develop branch

2ï¸âƒ£ Jenkins Trigger

Jenkins pipeline starts automatically via GitHub webhook

3ï¸âƒ£ Build Stage

Docker image is built using Dockerfile

4ï¸âƒ£ Push Stage

Image is pushed to Docker Hub with versioned tags

5ï¸âƒ£ Deploy Stage

Kubernetes deployment is updated using kubectl set image

Zero-downtime rollout handled by Kubernetes

ğŸ” Jenkins Credentials Used
Credential	Purpose
GitHub PAT	Repository access
Docker Hub creds	Push Docker images
kubeconfig	Access Kubernetes cluster


ğŸ“œ Sample Jenkinsfile Stages

Checkout Code

Build Docker Image

Push Image to Docker Hub

Deploy to Kubernetes (staging)

ğŸ› ï¸ Kubernetes Deployment

Uses Deployment resource

Runs inside staging namespace

Image updates handled via rolling updates

Supports scaling and rollback

ğŸ§ª Verification Commands
kubectl get pods -n staging
